{
  "text": "Fouilloux described, in his review [CITATION_1] , the existence of a variety of hydrogen species in Raney \u00aenickel catalysts. Using thermal desorption experiments, he found that H2 adsorbs onto the catalyst in reversible and irreversible forms. The two species may correspond to the bridged and linear adsorptions observed for hydrogenation using the neutron inelastic scattering technique. The strongly adsorbed hydrogen seems to be inactive in benzene, acetone, and acetonitrile hydrogenations, but the presence of weakly adsorbed linear hydrogen is crucial to the success of the reaction.",
  "citation_candidates": [
